## Unit I — Container Basics

### Q1. Deploy Apache httpd on port 8081
```powershell
docker pull httpd:alpine
docker images
docker run -d --name apache-web -p 8081:80 httpd:alpine
docker ps
curl.exe http://localhost:8081
```
**Browser:** http://localhost:8081

### Q2. Display custom message in Apache container
```powershell
docker run -d --name web-test -p 8080:80 httpd:alpine
docker exec web-test sh -c "echo '<h1>AMAN IS LEARNING DOCKER</h1>' > /usr/local/apache2/htdocs/index.html"
curl.exe http://localhost:8080
docker stop web-test; docker rm web-test
```

### Q3. Run MongoDB with port mapping
```powershell
# Host port 27017 → container port 27017
docker run -d --name DB-app -p 27017:27017 mongo:7
docker ps
```

### Q4. List all Docker object types
```powershell
docker images      # Images
docker ps -a       # Containers
docker network ls  # Networks
docker volume ls   # Volumes
```

