## Unit II — Dockerfile & Networking

### Q5. Build and run custom Node.js app
```powershell
cd labs\unit-2-dockerfile
docker build -t devops-node-lab:1.0 .
docker run -d --name node-lab -p 3000:3000 devops-node-lab:1.0
curl.exe http://localhost:3000
```

### Q6. Create custom network and connect containers
```powershell
docker network create app-network
docker run -d --name redis --network app-network redis:alpine
docker run -it --rm --network app-network alpine ping -c 3 redis
```

### Q7. Create named volume for persistence
```powershell
docker volume create mydata
docker run -d -v mydata:/data --name vol-test alpine sleep 3600
docker exec vol-test sh -c "echo persistent > /data/file.txt"
docker rm -f vol-test
docker run --rm -v mydata:/data alpine cat /data/file.txt
```

### Q8. Copy file from container to Windows Desktop
```powershell
docker run -d --name task nginx:alpine
docker exec task sh -c "mkdir -p /project && echo 'I am Learning Docker' > /project/notes.txt"
docker cp task:/project/notes.txt "$env:USERPROFILE\Desktop\notes.txt"
docker rm -f task
```

### Q9. Push image to GHCR
```powershell
docker build -t ghcr.io/YOUR_USERNAME/myapp:1.0 .
docker login ghcr.io -u YOUR_USERNAME
# Password: GitHub PAT (not account password)
docker push ghcr.io/YOUR_USERNAME/myapp:1.0
```

