## Unit VI — Jenkins

### Q15. Run Jenkins on Windows via Docker
```powershell
docker volume create jenkins_home
docker run -d -p 8080:8080 -p 50000:50000 `
  -v jenkins_home:/var/jenkins_home `
  --name jenkins-lab jenkins/jenkins:lts
docker exec jenkins-lab cat /var/jenkins_home/secrets/initialAdminPassword
```
**Browser:** http://localhost:8080

### Q16. Jenkins pipeline stages (typical)
1. Checkout (Git)
2. Build (Maven/npm)
3. Test (Surefire/JUnit)
4. Package (JAR/Docker image)
5. Deploy (SSH/cloud)
6. Post (always notify/cleanup)

